WEBVTT

01:12.247 --> 01:14.610
<i>Vehicle in the left lane</i>
<i>causing congestion, so...</i>

01:14.645 --> 01:16.678
-<i> ...avoid this route.</i>

01:16.713 --> 01:18.647
<i>Thank you for the morning</i>
<i>traffic update, John.</i>

01:18.682 --> 01:19.747
<i>You know, Fred, I always</i>

01:19.782 --> 01:21.617
<i>get this strange feeling</i>

01:21.652 --> 01:22.882
<i>when I'm stuck in traffic.</i>

01:22.917 --> 01:25.687
<i>There I am, mere feet</i>
<i>away from other people</i>

01:25.722 --> 01:27.788
<i>packed together</i>
<i>on a strip of asphalt.</i>

01:27.823 --> 01:30.197
<i>Yet we find ourselves</i>
<i>passing by each other</i>

01:30.232 --> 01:33.233
<i>from the loneliness</i>
<i>of our respective tin cans.</i>

01:35.633 --> 01:37.501
<i>You got the supply chain,</i>
<i>right?</i>

01:37.536 --> 01:39.371
<i>Transportation of goods</i>
<i>being...</i>

01:39.406 --> 01:42.242
<i>Your goal is to meet</i>
<i>your high-value objectives,</i>

01:42.277 --> 01:44.805
<i>ensure the supplier</i>
<i>feels good about the deal.</i>

01:48.217 --> 01:51.185
<i>Let's round off the hour</i>
<i>and welcome the rising sun</i>

01:51.220 --> 01:53.385
<i>with a song</i>
<i>that I'm sure you'll remember.</i>

02:09.634 --> 02:14.340
<i>♪ I got my looks</i>
<i>from my mama and dad ♪</i>

03:08.330 --> 03:10.429
<i>How is your morning, drivers?</i>

03:10.464 --> 03:12.464
<i>All good in Albany, ladies,</i>
<i>headin' south.</i>

03:12.499 --> 03:14.664
<i> Well, I pulled</i>
<i>an all-nighter out here,</i>

03:14.699 --> 03:16.270
<i>unloading in Sacramento.</i>

03:16.305 --> 03:17.436
<i>Mornin' over there yet?</i>

03:17.471 --> 03:19.405
<i>No, it's all dark here.</i>

03:19.440 --> 03:20.736
<i>Can't wait to head back East</i>

03:20.771 --> 03:23.574
<i>as soon as I get her</i>
<i>emptied out and loaded back up.</i>

03:23.609 --> 03:26.038
<i> Well, I got</i>
<i>a great view up in the Rockies,</i>

03:26.073 --> 03:28.876
<i>but the truth is</i>
<i>I'm just scared shitless</i>
<i>of the trip down.</i>

03:30.649 --> 03:32.319
<i>Break on the engine, sweetie.</i>

03:32.354 --> 03:33.820
<i> Jake break, driver.</i>

03:33.856 --> 03:37.423
<i> How about you, Sally?</i>
<i>Hey,</i> chiquita,<i> you still there?</i>

03:37.458 --> 03:41.658
Yeah, still here.
I got a beautiful day here.

03:41.693 --> 03:43.792
Heading east to 61.

03:43.827 --> 03:45.695
<i>Good to have you back, chica.</i>

03:45.730 --> 03:49.303
<i> Oh, shut up, Pattie.</i>
<i>She's Canadian, not Mexican.</i>

03:49.338 --> 03:51.668
<i> She talks weird.</i>
<i>That's all I know.</i>

03:51.703 --> 03:55.804
Okay, you're giving me shit,
you motherfuckers.

03:55.839 --> 03:58.642
- <i> Oh, yeah. You got it.</i>

03:58.677 --> 04:00.644
<i>You pickin' up</i>
<i>your brother today?</i>

04:00.679 --> 04:03.548
<i> No, Thursday.</i>
<i>Come on, Dolly.</i>

04:03.583 --> 04:05.781
<i>She ain't been talking</i>
<i>about anything else for weeks.</i>

04:05.816 --> 04:07.684
<i> Do he talk weird</i>
<i>like you, Sally?</i>

04:07.719 --> 04:10.390
Well, Dolly, fuck you very much.

04:10.425 --> 04:13.921
<i> Shut it.</i>
<i>You know he came down here</i>
<i>when he was real little.</i>

04:13.956 --> 04:15.758
<i>Sally came later.</i>

04:15.793 --> 04:17.826
<i> Yeah, right.</i>
<i>That's what fucked her up.</i>

04:17.861 --> 04:19.960
<i>No, that's what fucked him up.</i>

04:19.995 --> 04:23.062
Fuck you, too.
Okay, drivers. Gotta go.

04:23.097 --> 04:25.636
<i> Bye now.</i>
<i>Be safe. Safe.</i>

04:25.671 --> 04:27.473
- <i> Safe.</i>
- Safe.

04:56.999 --> 04:59.736
- <i> Yeah?</i>
- I'm here to visit.

05:05.139 --> 05:06.578
Thank you.

05:15.820 --> 05:19.591
I missed you so much.

05:19.626 --> 05:21.461
Take your seats, please.

05:24.565 --> 05:26.565
I have not been
this excited to see you

05:26.600 --> 05:28.798
since you came down
from Quebec with Mom.

05:38.106 --> 05:40.810
Pick you up Thursday?

05:40.845 --> 05:43.142
- You better.

05:43.177 --> 05:44.979
You got the "dress-out"
in the mail, right?

05:45.014 --> 05:46.013
Yeah.

05:48.820 --> 05:52.085
It's just so weird
because, uh...

05:52.120 --> 05:54.560
you know,
you cope while you're in here

05:54.595 --> 05:57.431
and... and when
it's almost over,

05:57.466 --> 05:59.158
then you just
can't take it anymore.

06:01.734 --> 06:03.767
It's kinda like
when you have to go
to the bathroom--

06:03.802 --> 06:06.869
- You're almost there,
and the door is locked.

06:06.904 --> 06:08.068
Sit back, please.

06:09.577 --> 06:10.609
It's her.

06:13.779 --> 06:16.648
Well, I know what I want.

06:18.080 --> 06:21.653
I want you to make me that...
tart tartu.

06:21.688 --> 06:23.787
- I want you
to make a tart tartu.

06:23.822 --> 06:26.493
What was it? What was it?

06:26.528 --> 06:27.890
What's that stuff Mom made?

06:27.925 --> 06:29.661
- Tarte Tatin.
- Tarte Tatin.

06:29.696 --> 06:31.597
- Apple tart.
- I love it.

06:53.852 --> 06:56.490
- Two minutes.

06:57.757 --> 06:58.756
Thursday.

07:05.193 --> 07:08.161
What? Please, you said
that was the last time.

07:09.637 --> 07:13.133
- They asked for one more.

07:13.168 --> 07:15.168
I know, I know, I know.
I gotta get on the outside.

07:15.203 --> 07:16.708
You gotta get me on the outside.
Okay?

07:16.743 --> 07:18.512
- Just one more time.

07:18.547 --> 07:20.877
- So, last package, I promise.
- Okay.

07:20.912 --> 07:23.209
All right? We ain't bad.
We ain't bad.

07:23.244 --> 07:24.881
Listen, listen, listen.

07:24.916 --> 07:26.520
All visitors
must exit now.

07:26.555 --> 07:27.983
They're gonna fucking kill me.
Sis, you gotta get me

07:28.018 --> 07:29.820
- out of here, okay?
- Okay, yeah, yeah.

08:45.392 --> 08:47.095
Where's the package?

08:49.671 --> 08:51.935
What the fuck?

08:51.970 --> 08:54.201
You'll take her there.
Across the state line.

08:54.236 --> 08:55.609
Paul's the guy
who's gonna meet you.

08:55.644 --> 08:57.941
Come on, sweetie.

09:00.308 --> 09:01.648
Yep.

09:02.948 --> 09:07.247
No way.
No fucking way.

09:07.282 --> 09:10.987
- Excuse me?
- You don't understand.
I don't take people.

09:12.925 --> 09:16.223
Hey!
I was told I could trust you.

09:16.258 --> 09:18.632
No way I can promise
what'll happen to your brother

09:18.667 --> 09:21.294
if you don't take the girl
where she fucking needs to go!

10:02.370 --> 10:04.040
What's your name?

10:05.406 --> 10:07.241
We're not gonna talk.

12:27.449 --> 12:28.448
Paul?

12:29.924 --> 12:31.022
Yep.

12:33.356 --> 12:34.960
Come on, lady.
It's paid fo--

12:43.938 --> 12:45.399
No! Get off of me!

12:48.943 --> 12:51.977
- Fuck! Fuck! Get down!

13:41.655 --> 13:43.622
Fuck!

13:43.657 --> 13:46.262
- Shut up!

13:49.366 --> 13:54.006
Northbound...
can I get a radio check?

13:54.041 --> 13:56.206
Any bears at the weigh station?

13:57.605 --> 13:59.539
Any bears at the weigh--

13:59.574 --> 14:02.377
The fucking fuse!

14:02.412 --> 14:05.347
- Get down! Get down!
- No!

14:08.385 --> 14:11.518
They can search
the entire truck. Get down!

14:11.553 --> 14:13.388
No! Stop!

14:15.722 --> 14:18.360
Police! Police!

14:18.395 --> 14:20.065
Is that what you want?

16:19.318 --> 16:21.384
All right, kids,
run to the bathroom.

16:22.717 --> 16:24.255
We gotta get you in the back.

16:24.290 --> 16:26.488
Come on. Come on.

16:27.623 --> 16:29.128
- Come on.

16:31.198 --> 16:32.494
Stop!

16:35.829 --> 16:38.203
- No! No!
- Come on!

16:38.238 --> 16:40.733
- Shh.

16:40.768 --> 16:43.670
- Let's go, guys.
Come on. Hurry--

16:47.346 --> 16:49.313
You're gonna miss
Nia's birthday.

17:57.185 --> 17:58.811
- Mornin'.
- Mornin'.

18:03.488 --> 18:06.159
- In, in, in, in.
Quick, quick.

18:09.197 --> 18:10.427
Seatbelts.

18:39.293 --> 18:41.194
- Dennis?
- <i> I'm sorry.</i>

18:41.229 --> 18:43.493
<i>Took some time to get</i>
<i>a burner phone. You okay?</i>

18:43.528 --> 18:46.496
- It was a girl, Dennis.
<i>- What do you mean?</i>

18:46.531 --> 18:50.599
Young. Ten, 12 maybe.

18:50.634 --> 18:52.370
<i>Wait, what, what?</i>
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

18:52.405 --> 18:54.438
The fucking package was a girl.

18:56.002 --> 19:00.279
<i>What? Oh, fuck.</i>
<i>What did you do?</i>

19:01.480 --> 19:03.249
She shot the guy.

19:03.284 --> 19:04.811
With your shotgun.

19:04.846 --> 19:08.716
<i>Oh, my God.</i>
<i>Is he dead?</i>

19:09.752 --> 19:11.686
I don't know. I think so. I--

19:11.721 --> 19:15.921
<i>Oh, we're so fucked.</i>
<i>What are we gonna do?</i>

19:15.956 --> 19:18.528
<i>- What-what are you hauling?</i>
- Unloading in Oxford.

19:18.563 --> 19:20.530
Got another taking me
to Jackson. That's it.

19:20.565 --> 19:21.927
<i>Okay, all right,</i>
<i>you just listen.</i>

19:21.962 --> 19:23.731
<i>Just seem--</i>
<i>just seem regular, you know.</i>

19:23.766 --> 19:25.865
<i>Just finish</i>
<i>whatever bookings you got.</i>

19:25.900 --> 19:27.933
Are you gonna be okay?

19:27.968 --> 19:29.803
<i>You're in danger, sis.</i>

19:29.838 --> 19:32.608
<i>These guys have eyes</i>
<i>all over the fucking state.</i>

19:34.007 --> 19:36.678
And the girl...
where do I drop the girl?

19:36.713 --> 19:38.779
<i>I don't know, I don't know.</i>
<i>You just gotta take her--</i>
<i>take her with you.</i>

19:38.814 --> 19:40.583
- What?
-<i> I-I don't know.</i>

19:40.618 --> 19:43.784
No! No way she can
stay in my truck.

19:43.819 --> 19:45.885
<i>She's the only thing</i>
<i>keepin' us safe.</i>

20:43.516 --> 20:47.419
Hey, beautiful.
- Fuck off! Motherfucker!

22:37.157 --> 22:38.959
He just...

22:39.995 --> 22:42.028
He exploded.

23:43.597 --> 23:45.223
This is your guy, right?

23:45.258 --> 23:49.865
Fuck. Yeah,
I took him down a half year ago

23:49.900 --> 23:53.066
when we busted
the MacDougal traffic ring.

23:53.101 --> 23:57.037
Low level sergeant,
oversaw one of the routes.

23:59.074 --> 24:01.679
- He's out already?
- Out on bond.

24:03.078 --> 24:05.716
Pictures of those girls
still haunt the web.

24:07.951 --> 24:10.182
Shell casings? Prints?

24:10.217 --> 24:12.558
Fingerprints
only from the victim.

24:13.891 --> 24:16.155
They ended him with a slug.

24:17.895 --> 24:20.126
- Nasty choice for a hit job.
- Hmm.

24:20.161 --> 24:22.161
Other slug's
in that tree over there.

24:23.604 --> 24:26.132
And you're retired
for how long now?

24:28.037 --> 24:30.169
Consultant Gerick
at your service.

24:30.204 --> 24:34.646
So, who's your new assistant?

24:34.681 --> 24:36.846
Ah, desk rat from legal.

24:36.881 --> 24:40.718
Wants field experience.
Went to Yale.

24:40.753 --> 24:42.951
I heard they have a very good
English department.

24:42.986 --> 24:44.590
Mm.

24:47.254 --> 24:48.693
Strange.

24:50.356 --> 24:51.322
Paul came here

24:51.357 --> 24:53.632
to pick up a girl

24:53.667 --> 24:56.327
who'd been transported
across the state line.

24:56.362 --> 24:58.571
His normal routine.
But then...

25:00.135 --> 25:02.135
Why?

25:02.170 --> 25:04.676
It's what we're
trying to figure out.

25:04.711 --> 25:07.712
We got wider and deeper tracks
from the second vehicle.

25:07.747 --> 25:09.010
It's probably a truck.

25:09.045 --> 25:13.113
Yeah. Refrigerated trailer
or dry van.

25:13.148 --> 25:15.346
No tarp.

25:15.381 --> 25:19.658
All right, well,
start by alerting
the weigh stations, Finley.

25:19.693 --> 25:22.628
Excuse me, Gerick. Just, please,
call me by my last name.

25:22.663 --> 25:25.092
- All right, Yale.
- Sterling.

25:25.127 --> 25:27.699
You gonna make those calls
or you gonna write a poem
about it?

25:29.098 --> 25:31.230
I'll make the calls.
Just, please, call me Sterling.

25:31.265 --> 25:32.803
Yeah.

25:55.861 --> 25:58.224
Never seen you so lazy,
Ms. Sally.

25:58.259 --> 25:59.995
Sorry, Frank, got a bad knee.

26:01.966 --> 26:03.295
You got a lover in there, huh?

26:03.330 --> 26:05.198
Always.

26:05.233 --> 26:09.774
Uh-huh. Well, you ready to roll.

27:04.897 --> 27:06.061
Take these out to the car.

27:06.096 --> 27:07.458
- Whoa.

27:07.493 --> 27:10.131
- Come on, come on.
- Fine.

27:10.166 --> 27:11.330
All right.

27:11.365 --> 27:13.365
Hey, so, State Police

27:13.400 --> 27:15.070
are doing us a favor
on the weigh stations,

27:15.105 --> 27:16.940
and we got a match
on the muddy tire tracks

27:16.975 --> 27:18.370
headed onto
the south highway entrance.

27:18.405 --> 27:19.943
So Mississippi, not Tennessee.

27:19.978 --> 27:22.044
- And--
- Here.

27:22.079 --> 27:24.475
Yeah, Gerick,
I'm not your assistant.

27:24.510 --> 27:27.412
This is my case,
and I appreciate having you
on as a consultant,

27:27.447 --> 27:29.447
but right now, we just need you
to sign this, and then--

27:29.482 --> 27:31.449
We start with files
from last year.

27:31.484 --> 27:34.287
I'll bet he was whacked by
one of his little buddies.

27:34.322 --> 27:37.290
We take a look at
all known associates.

27:37.325 --> 27:40.260
Find out which one
might've had a beef with Paul.

27:40.295 --> 27:42.262
And we're looking for a girl.
One.

27:42.297 --> 27:44.495
He always bought 'em
one at a time.

27:44.530 --> 27:47.234
Yeah, so we just need you
to sign this report
for headquarters.

27:47.269 --> 27:50.039
- No time for bureaucracy, Yale.

27:50.074 --> 27:53.339
I think you're taking this
a bit too personally, sir.

27:53.374 --> 27:55.880
- Excuse me?
- I think you heard me.

27:59.446 --> 28:01.182
All right. We're taking my car.

28:01.217 --> 28:04.416
And let me know where
we're at with that cell phone.

28:10.160 --> 28:12.028
Okay, so we
did crack Paul's phone.

28:12.063 --> 28:14.261
It wasn't easy.
With recent numbers
already being dead,

28:14.296 --> 28:16.131
we couldn't trace it,
and no registered address.

28:16.166 --> 28:17.803
But he did pay for
the phone bill
with a credit card

28:17.838 --> 28:20.366
that also paid the utilities
at an address.

28:20.401 --> 28:22.973
Good lung capacity there,
Yale.

28:23.008 --> 28:25.041
What is that,
Ivy League swim team?

28:25.076 --> 28:26.977
I put in a request
for a warrant.

28:27.012 --> 28:29.012
- Ah, we're not
waiting for that.
- Gerick.

28:32.083 --> 28:33.280
Something's not right.

28:34.888 --> 28:36.547
Paul should've called by now.

28:50.596 --> 28:52.035
Go back to your room!

29:08.218 --> 29:10.482
Be smart.
Stay in the back.

29:11.617 --> 29:13.551
Don't let anybody see you, okay?

30:03.372 --> 30:06.604
Hey! Hey, you! Hey!

30:12.953 --> 30:14.612
- Who's that girl?

30:14.647 --> 30:17.054
What the fuck are you doing?
- Goddamnit!

30:17.089 --> 30:20.354
Does anyone care
that I am working next door?

30:28.628 --> 30:30.496
All right.

30:33.336 --> 30:37.437
Okay. Let's get goin'.

30:46.646 --> 30:48.448
I always move the truck

30:48.483 --> 30:51.517
after being seen
outside of this truck stop.

30:51.552 --> 30:54.190
Worst reputation on the road.

30:57.657 --> 31:00.900
Hmm. My brother. He's good.

31:02.002 --> 31:04.563
Champ. He'll help.

31:20.086 --> 31:21.415
You got a brother?

31:23.353 --> 31:24.583
Sisters?

31:32.131 --> 31:34.967
Guess you don't have
no mom or dad either, huh?

31:35.002 --> 31:37.266
What are you? Baby Jesus?

31:39.534 --> 31:40.973
What's your name?

31:43.670 --> 31:44.977
Leila.

31:45.012 --> 31:46.077
Leila.

31:48.774 --> 31:50.609
<i> And that was the</i>
<i>farmer who found the body</i>

31:50.644 --> 31:53.513
<i>- on a muddy back road off 25.</i>
- Mm-hm. I see it.

31:53.548 --> 31:55.680
<i>- Less than a mile north</i>
<i>of the state border.</i>
Yeah.

31:55.715 --> 31:58.584
<i>A brutal killing</i>
<i>that's hard to grapple with.</i>

31:58.619 --> 32:01.620
<i>- How did it happen and why?</i>
- That little girl's
gonna tell on us.

32:01.655 --> 32:04.326
No one's gonna tell on nobody.

32:04.361 --> 32:08.033
<i> The once quiet</i>
<i>community is coming to terms</i>
<i>with what's happened</i>

32:08.068 --> 32:11.168
<i>as the motive remains unclear</i>
<i>in the Mud Murder.</i>

32:11.203 --> 32:14.501
<i>What would warrant</i>
<i>such a violent end</i>
<i>to a person's life?</i>

32:14.536 --> 32:16.338
<i>Law enforcement is questioning</i>

32:16.373 --> 32:18.472
<i>- the use of slugs...</i>
- Fuck me. Who leaked?

32:18.507 --> 32:20.375
<i>- ...a particularly</i>
<i>damaging bullet.</i>
Not me.

32:20.410 --> 32:22.509
<i>It's a most unusual find</i>
<i>at the crime scene.</i>

32:22.544 --> 32:26.315
Some lonesome cowboy
wanting his 15 minutes of fame.

32:26.350 --> 32:27.613
<i>...police are</i>
<i>looking into the manner.</i>

32:27.648 --> 32:29.285
<i>And this, for now,</i>
<i>is all we know</i>

32:29.320 --> 32:30.748
<i>about the innocent victim.</i>

32:30.783 --> 32:32.585
Innocent, my ass.

32:32.620 --> 32:34.719
<i>As the investigation proceeds,</i>

32:34.754 --> 32:36.655
<i>no stone will be left unturned.</i>

32:36.690 --> 32:38.558
You can go to the police,

32:38.593 --> 32:41.429
tell 'em what he
would've done to you.

32:43.103 --> 32:45.136
That it was self-defense.

32:47.239 --> 32:48.405
Hmm?

32:48.440 --> 32:50.636
<i> ...is where</i>
<i>the crime took place,</i>

32:50.671 --> 32:52.638
<i>spreading fear on what...</i>

32:52.673 --> 32:54.805
Just don't bite and kick 'em,
all right?

32:54.840 --> 32:58.050
<i>...still hiding in the woods.</i>

32:58.085 --> 32:59.414
<i>It's not yet confirmed...</i>

32:59.449 --> 33:02.417
I don't like the police.

33:02.452 --> 33:06.355
<i>...but it is confirmed that</i>
<i>the manhunt covers both states.</i>

33:18.765 --> 33:22.371
You crying 'cause you're scared,
or you crying 'cause
that piece of shit is dead?

33:26.245 --> 33:28.476
You know, Leila,
you might have shot him,

33:28.511 --> 33:30.577
but I left him there to die.

33:33.153 --> 33:36.055
- We're in this together.

33:46.859 --> 33:49.431
Oh, we can't
cross state lines.

33:49.466 --> 33:51.664
It's too risky
with the weigh stations.

33:54.636 --> 33:56.636
Mm-mm.

33:56.671 --> 33:59.606
