you had a niece.

46:03.001 --> 46:08.235
Oh, come on, Patterson,
don't give me this shit about
priority of resources, man.

46:08.270 --> 46:12.107
This is a fucking priority.
Fuck!

46:21.646 --> 46:23.349
Fuck!

46:23.384 --> 46:24.823
- Yeah.
- Fuck!

46:27.421 --> 46:30.961
You've been at this, what,
30, 40 years?

46:31.964 --> 46:33.062
Fifty.

46:35.231 --> 46:36.967
Still gets you riled up, huh?

46:37.970 --> 46:39.904
How the hell can it not?

46:45.043 --> 46:46.471
Why don't they run?

46:48.574 --> 46:52.312
You know? Because I would.

46:52.347 --> 46:54.380
Anything to get away
from that hellhole.

46:54.415 --> 46:58.516
Fuck no. You--
you'd be locked in a basement.

47:01.323 --> 47:05.061
No, you wouldn't run.
You'd stay.

47:06.361 --> 47:10.627
Try to play the game.
Survive.

47:12.939 --> 47:14.433
What the fuck would you
live on out there?

47:14.468 --> 47:16.501
Grass? Clover?

47:18.010 --> 47:19.109
Best case scenario,

47:19.145 --> 47:21.605
you're found and brought
right back into the system.

47:21.640 --> 47:23.475
Then you'd run again.

47:28.350 --> 47:29.613
Sorry.

47:32.684 --> 47:35.058
Most of these kids
are held captive

47:35.093 --> 47:38.160
just a few miles
from where they grew up.

47:38.195 --> 47:40.624
In their minds
they got nowhere to go.

47:43.332 --> 47:45.937
And for a lot of 'em,
that's true.

47:50.273 --> 47:51.635
Same hair
as in the basement.

47:53.540 --> 47:54.913
Thank you.

48:16.596 --> 48:18.695
Shouldn't we get--
shouldn't we get rid of that?

48:18.730 --> 48:23.172
Not an option. My mom gave it
to my brother before she died.

48:24.241 --> 48:27.011
They find this...

48:27.046 --> 48:28.540
they've found us anyway.

48:31.578 --> 48:33.479
You fire it, you clean it.

48:48.496 --> 48:50.430
I see his eyes all the time.

48:52.566 --> 48:55.072
You kill someone
'cause you wanna be free,

48:56.075 --> 48:57.734
but then he still gets you.

49:00.409 --> 49:02.211
How'd you learn to shoot?

49:09.616 --> 49:11.088
This guy Cooper.

49:12.685 --> 49:15.125
My mom left me with him
when she went to work.

49:16.359 --> 49:18.425
He was buildin' an armory.

49:20.792 --> 49:25.135
He always said
if the world went to shit...
he'd be ready.

50:08.840 --> 50:10.576
Do you ever feel lonely?

50:12.481 --> 50:13.645
Always.

50:52.323 --> 50:53.718
Just a few gallons of gas.

50:53.753 --> 50:55.126
